## Instructions

1. Heat olive oil in a large pot or deep skillet over medium heat. Add sausage, breaking it up with a spoon, and cook until browned, about 5 minutes.
2. Add onion and garlic, cook until softened, about 3 minutes.
3. Stir in crushed tomatoes, chicken broth, red pepper flakes, salt, and pepper.
4. Add the dry pasta directly to the pot, stirring to submerge it in the liquid.
5. Bring to a simmer, then cover and cook for 15–18 minutes, stirring occasionally, until pasta is tender and most of the liquid is absorbed.
6. Remove from heat, stir in parmesan, and top with fresh basil before serving.

## Notes

If the sauce looks too thick before the pasta is fully cooked, splash in a bit more broth or water. Ground beef or turkey work fine in place of sausage — just add a little extra salt and Italian seasoning.
